{"cursor":"1642","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Speciesbox\n| taxon = Allium cristophii image = Allium albopilosum.jpg image_caption =\n| Illustration of Allium albopilosum authority = Trautv.\n}}\n\n'Allium cristophii' ('Persian Onion', 'Star of Persia'; [http://www.ars-grin.gov/cgi-\nbin/npgs/html/taxon.pl?406525 Allium cristophii] at [http://www.ars-grin.gov/\nGermplasm Resources Information Network] syn. Allium albopilosum\n[http://www.gardening.cornell.edu/homegardening/scenec7fd.html Allium\ncristophii] at [http://www.gardening.cornell.edu/homegardening/scenee139.html\nFlower Growing Guides] of Cornell University ) is an ornamental bulbous\nplant of the Allioideae subfamily of the Amaryllidaceae. It grows to 60 cm\n(24\") and is cultivated in gardens for its large showy heads (umbels) of silvery\npink star-shaped flowers, 20â25 cm (8-10\") in diameter, which appear in\nearly summer. The flowers are followed by attractive seed-heads. The plant has\nreceived the Royal Horticultural Society's Award of Garden Merit. [http://www.rhs.org.uk/Gardens/Harlow-Carr/About-Harlow-Carr/Plant-\nof-the-month/May/Allium-cristophii Allium cristophii]\n","linknr":231,"url":"Star_of_Persia","recorded":1375056609,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Allium_cristophii&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Allium_cristophii&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Allium_cristophii","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikime